   <conbody>
      <p class="- topic/p ">
         <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Qualifications &amp; Benefits</b> feature enables you to add products or categories for which you want to provide benefits.</p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">In the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">New Program</b> page, you can view the following options for <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Default Qualification Formula</b>:</p>
      <ul class="- topic/ul ">
         <li class="- topic/li ">Volume Tier</li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">Multiple Qualifications</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="- topic/p ">
         <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Volume Tier Qualifications</b>
      </p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">For more information about Volume Tiered qualifications and benefits, please refer to the <xref href="../qualifications_and_benefi_102432700/102432700.dita"
               format="dita"
               class="- topic/xref ">Qualifications and Benefits</xref> section.</p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">
         <fig class="- topic/fig ">
            <image placement="break"
                   width="750"
                   href="../attachments/102432706/107118656.jpg"
                   class="- topic/image "/>
         </fig>
      </p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">You can provide the following information on the Qualifications and Benefits page for Tiered programs:</p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">
         <table class="- topic/table ">
            <tgroup cols="2" class="- topic/tgroup ">
               <colspec colname="col1" class="- topic/colspec "/>
               <colspec colname="col2" class="- topic/colspec "/>
               <thead class="- topic/thead ">
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Fields</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Description</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
               </thead>
               <tbody class="- topic/tbody ">
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">
                           <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Product Name</b>
                        </p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Add products or categories in the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Product Name</b> column. For adding products or categories, please refer to the <xref href="../adding-products_102432695_102432695/102432695.dita"
                                 format="dita"
                                 class="- topic/xref ">Adding Products</xref> section. Products are the list of products that are purchased by the customer.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">
                           <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Number of Tiers</b>
                        </p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Enter the number of tiers. For example, 1,2, or 3. If you enter value 2, then the corresponding list will have Tier 1 and Tier 2 columns.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">
                           <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Tier1 or Tier 2</b>
                        </p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">The value provided in the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Tiers</b> is the minimum value of the product which the customer has to purchase. For example, if the value in <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Tier 1</b> is 20, it means, if the customers want to achieve tier 1, then they have to buy the product's volume anything which is greater than or equal to 20 or less than 25 and the price given is 200$. 25 is the Tier 2 volume considered in this example, see the above image. Any product's volume which is greater than 25, which is tier 2 value, will be given for 180$.</p>
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Hence, the value given in a particular tier is the lower value and the higher value is anything which is less than the next tier.</p>
                        <p class="- topic/p ">If more than one participants purchase the same products then the Tier value will be decided based on the aggregated products' volume.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">
                           <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Price</b>
                        </p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Price of the products defined for a particular tier.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">
                           <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Qualification Product not same as Benefit Product checkbox</b>
                        </p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">When you select this checkbox you are mentioning that qualification product is different than benefit products.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">
                           <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Save</b>
                        </p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Click <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Save</b> to save the made changes.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
               </tbody>
            </tgroup>
         </table>
      </p>
      <note type="note" class="- topic/note ">In the Qualification and Benefits page, if you select CPG for qualifications products similarly you can view the CPG products in the Benefits products.</note>
